            "answer_text": "There are many libraries which you can use to export Excel files or you can even use the Python CSV module. There's a list for Excel libraries: Python Excel, which also links to documentations and source codes.It depends on what data you want to save, for example, if you want to make charts automatically, you can use xlsxwriter. For more details on how to do this, you can checkout his article: How to export Excel files in a Python/Django application. It's also easy to learn. ",
